DISCUSSION ffle generic assignment of
Cyphocharax albiventris
is supported by the expanded multilocus phylogeny of the Curimatidae (g. 3) (sensu
), and the lack of the derived characters supporting other nominal genera, such as
Curimatella
(the
Cyphocharax sensu Vari, 1989a
,
). Our results also indicate that
Cy. albiventris
is a member of the
Curimatella alburna
clade (
,
), a group hypothesized to have undergone initial diversi cation between 37 and 25 million years ago (
). ffle position of
Cy. albiventris
as sister to a broader group of species in the clade suggests that the cladogenetic event that led to species’ evolutionary origin may have occurred prior to the Miocene channelization of the Rio Amazonas (
;
).

