Using integrative taxonomy approaches in curimatids has recently aided in overcoming these obstacles (

, 2018, 2022; 

), which has not only aided in the recognition of cryptic species but also in the di erentiation of phenotypically similar ones (i.e., 

Cy. gouldingi

and 

Cy. spiluropsis

). fflat was the case in this contribution, where 

Cy. albiventris

was unambiguously delimited from other congeneric species by the two methods used, so assisting the description of a new species (gs. 3, 4).

